/i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Paveley II was born in 1125, in Paulerspury, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of Robert Paveley I. He had at least 1 son. He died after 1170, in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1125–after 1170":"1125–pärast 1170","1125–1170":"1125–1170","–1196":"–1196","1095–1129":"1095–1129","1129":"1129","after 1129":"pärast 1129","1125":"1125","after 1170":"pärast 1170","1196":"1196","1095":"1095","1170":"1170","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Paulerspury, Potterspury, Northamptonshire, England":"Paulerspury, Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1125–after 1170":"1125–1170 jälkeen","1125–1170":"1125–1170","–1196":"–1196","1095–1129":"1095–1129","1129":"1129","after 1129":"1129 jälkeen","1125":"1125","after 1170":"1170 jälkeen","1196":"1196","1095":"1095","1170":"1170","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Paulerspury, Potterspury, Northamptonshire, England":"Paulerspury, Northamptonshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1125–after 1170":"1125–après 1170","1125–1170":"1125–1170","–1196":"–1196","1095–1129":"1095–1129","1129":"1129","after 1129":"après 1129","1125":"1125","after 1170":"après 1170","1196":"1196","1095":"1095","1170":"1170","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Paulerspury, Potterspury, Northamptonshire, England":"Paulerspury, Northamptonshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Robert Paveley II est né en 1125, à Paulerspury, Northampt